mod_auth_httprequest
  Copyright 2010, Toshiyuki Suzumura, under Apache License, Version 2.0
      http://github.com/suzumura-ss/mod_auth_httprequest
      http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0


- Input request headers:
  All headers is bypassed to request to `X-Auth-HttpRequest-URI`

- Output request headers, when "OK", "Created", "Accepted":
  Following request headers are appended.
    ENV['REMOTE_USER']   `HttpRequestAuth-RequestURI` string.
    ENV['AUTH_TYPE']     "X-Auth-HttpRequest-URI".

- Output response headers and body, authentication failed:
  All headers are bypassed to response.
  Original request is not requested.


Directive commands:
  Require   valid-request       Use this authentication.
  AuthType  AuthHttpRequest     Use this authentication.
  AuthName  X-Auth-HttpRequest  (ignored)

  HttpRequestAuth-RequestURI    uri             Authentication request URI.
                                                Default: locaslhost/requested-path
  HttpRequestAuth-Secret        filename        Binary data to detect recursive request.
  HttpRequestAuth-ErrorDocument string or URL   Custom error document. "%d" as response code.
                                                Default: apache default.
